    "what_description": "Angelica dentata is a perennial plant that belongs to the family Apiaceae. It is characterized by its deeply divided, toothed leaves, typically 3-5 pinnate, with leaflets that are linear-lanceolate in shape. The plant can grow up to 1.5 meters tall, with a stout, hairy stem and a taproot. It produces small, white or yellowish flowers in umbrella-like umbels, which are 2-3 cm in diameter, from June to August. The plant is native to China and Japan, and is also found in parts of Eastern Asia, where it grows in moist, mountainous regions.",
