    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Angelica dentata are its antioxidant capacity, which is attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids. This plant also exhibits antimicrobial activity, inhibiting the growth of various pathogens due to the bioactive compounds saponins and volatile oils. Anti-inflammatory effects of Angelica dentata are thought to be mediated by sesquiterpenes and phenolic compounds, reducing inflammation and alleviating associated symptoms. Additionally, the hepatoprotective properties of this plant are attributed to its ability to scavenge free radicals and modulate liver enzymes, protecting liver cells from damage. The analgesic properties of Angelica dentata are likely due to the presence of sesquiterpenes and phenolic compounds, which may help alleviate pain by inhibiting the release of pro-inflammatory mediators.",
